n errors compute; VFE F-total=0.40 (mostly complexity from uniform priors); multi-step runs 3 steps without early-termination; final belief differs from uniform.\n\n**Adjacent bug-fix in `arxana-vsatarcs-trace.el`:** `follow-wm` previously emitted ticks to today's wall-clock VSATARCS trace file (via `emit`'s default path), not the date being followed. Two trace tests (`follow-wm-timestamps-align-with-wm`, `follow-wm-picks-up-new-records`) surfaced this when the wall clock crossed midnight UTC during this session. Fixed by having follow-wm pass the date-specific path explicitly: a VSATARCS tick now lands in the same day-bucket as the WM record it follows, regardless of when `follow-wm` runs. Honest follow-up on the 'docs always in line with code' guarantee."
