ht-all', stores the next state in the emitted record.  Pure additive wiring; no breaking changes to existing trace fields.\n\n**Two bugs caught + fixed during authoring:**\n  - `precision-reweight-all' plist construction order — push-channel-then-value rather than push-value-then-channel (so `(plist-get out :c1)' actually works).  Initial implementation was wrong; one test caught it.\n  - One test assertion expected `precision = cap' under constant errors; corrected to `precision = 1/min-variance' (the variance-component ceiling without need-component contribution).  Floor/cap bounds are the *outer* envelope; the variance-component-only ceiling lives at 1/min-variance = 100 (cap = 200 only reachable with need-component, which awaits preferences)."
