  - `:contract-status-section-update` (L4 candidate per M-vsatarcs-writer §1; future): proposed-text not already present in target section.

  **The admissibility predicate IS the recursion-safety property.**  When an action class produces output that becomes input to the same class (the recursive case — e.g., proposing a revision entry that documents the very landing of `:aif-edn-revision-entry`), the admissibility predicate detects the duplicate on the second pass and `can-propose?' returns nil.  Apparatus terminates self-application via the same predicate the operator-confirm path uses; no separate cycle-detector, no recursion-depth counter, no ad-hoc guard.

  **Generalisation to non-self-documentation classes** (e.g., the higher-blast-radius `:xtdb-hyperedge-emit' claude-2 holds for after L4 stabilises): admissibility predicate is class-specific but the *pattern* — clean-match AND structural-admissibility-against-target-state — transfers.  For `:xtdb-hyperedge-emit', plausible admissibility candidates include: hyperedge-id not already present in XTDB; or: payload not identical to a recent emission within some window.  The recursive-self-landing test on L4 validates that the pattern's safety mechanic works under maximal self-reference; downstream classes inherit the validated mechanic."
